    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Mutating in `groupby` takes a complicated code path, to be honest not sure if this is a bug a not.\r\n\r\nEasy workaround is to use `concat` to combine the modified frames.\r\n\r\n```python\r\n\r\ndef add_zero(row, name):\r\n    row.loc[name, 'b0'] = 0\r\n    return row\r\n\r\npd.concat([add_zero(row, name) \r\n           for name, row in az['Vals'].groupby(level='A')])\r\n\r\nOut[30]: \r\nA   B \r\na1  b1    0.006314\r\n    b2   -1.301589\r\n    b0    0.000000\r\na2  b3   -0.172631\r\n    b0    0.000000\r\na3  b4   -0.130576\r\n    b0    0.000000\r\nName: Vals, dtype: float64\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n"
  },
